domains.description: This domain is deprecated - use Runtime or Log instead.

properties.name: line
properties.description: Line number in the resource that generated this message (1-based).

properties.name: column
properties.description: Column number in the resource that generated this message (1-based).

commands.name: clearMessages
commands.description: Does nothing.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables console domain, prevents further console messages from being reported to the client.

commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enables console domain, sends the messages collected so far to the client by means of the
`messageAdded` notification.

events.name: messageAdded
events.description: Issued when new console message is added.

parameters.name: message
parameters.description: Console message that has been added.

domains.description:
Debugger domain exposes JavaScript debugging capabilities. It allows setting and removing
breakpoints, stepping through execution, exploring stack traces, etc.

properties.name: scriptId
properties.description: Script identifier as reported in the `Debugger.scriptParsed`.

types.description: JavaScript call frame. Array of call frames form the call stack.

properties.name: callFrameId
properties.description: Call frame identifier. This identifier is only valid while the virtual machine is paused.

properties.name: functionName
properties.description: Name of the JavaScript function called on this call frame.

properties.name: scopeChain
properties.description: Scope chain for this call frame.

properties.name: returnValue
properties.description: The value being returned, if the function is at return point.

properties.name: object
properties.description:
Object representing the scope. For `global` and `with` scopes it represents the actual
object; for the rest of the scopes, it is artificial transient object enumerating scope
variables as its properties.

properties.name: startLocation
properties.description: Location in the source code where scope starts

properties.name: endLocation
properties.description: Location in the source code where scope ends

properties.name: scriptId
properties.description: Script identifier as reported in the `Debugger.scriptParsed`.

commands.name: continueToLocation
commands.description: Continues execution until specific location is reached.

parameters.name: location
parameters.description: Location to continue to.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables debugger for given page.

commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enables debugger for the given page. Clients should not assume that the debugging has been
enabled until the result for this command is received.

commands.name: evaluateOnCallFrame
commands.description: Evaluates expression on a given call frame.

parameters.name: callFrameId
parameters.description: Call frame identifier to evaluate on.

parameters.name: expression
parameters.description: Expression to evaluate.

parameters.name: objectGroup
parameters.description:
String object group name to put result into (allows rapid releasing resulting object handles
using `releaseObjectGroup`).

parameters.name: includeCommandLineAPI
parameters.description:
Specifies whether command line API should be available to the evaluated expression, defaults
to false.

parameters.name: silent
parameters.description:
In silent mode exceptions thrown during evaluation are not reported and do not pause
execution. Overrides `setPauseOnException` state.

parameters.name: returnByValue
parameters.description: Whether the result is expected to be a JSON object that should be sent by value.

parameters.name: generatePreview
parameters.description: Whether preview should be generated for the result.

parameters.name: throwOnSideEffect
parameters.description: Whether to throw an exception if side effect cannot be ruled out during evaluation.

returns.name: result
returns.description: Object wrapper for the evaluation result.

commands.name: getPossibleBreakpoints
commands.description:
Returns possible locations for breakpoint. scriptId in start and end range locations should be
the same.

parameters.name: start
parameters.description: Start of range to search possible breakpoint locations in.

parameters.name: end
parameters.description:
End of range to search possible breakpoint locations in (excluding). When not specified, end
of scripts is used as end of range.

parameters.name: restrictToFunction
parameters.description: Only consider locations which are in the same (non-nested) function as start.

returns.name: locations
returns.description: List of the possible breakpoint locations.

commands.name: getScriptSource
commands.description: Returns source for the script with given id.

parameters.name: scriptId
parameters.description: Id of the script to get source for.

commands.name: getStackTrace
commands.description: Returns stack trace with given `stackTraceId`.

commands.name: pause
commands.description: Stops on the next JavaScript statement.

parameters.name: parentStackTraceId
parameters.description: Debugger will pause when async call with given stack trace is started.

commands.name: removeBreakpoint
commands.description: Removes JavaScript breakpoint.

commands.name: restartFrame
commands.description: Restarts particular call frame from the beginning.

parameters.name: callFrameId
parameters.description: Call frame identifier to evaluate on.

commands.name: resume
commands.description: Resumes JavaScript execution.

commands.name: scheduleStepIntoAsync
commands.description:
This method is deprecated - use Debugger.stepInto with breakOnAsyncCall and
Debugger.pauseOnAsyncTask instead. Steps into next scheduled async task if any is scheduled
before next pause. Returns success when async task is actually scheduled, returns error if no
task were scheduled or another scheduleStepIntoAsync was called.

commands.name: searchInContent
commands.description: Searches for given string in script content.

parameters.name: scriptId
parameters.description: Id of the script to search in.

parameters.name: query
parameters.description: String to search for.

parameters.name: caseSensitive
parameters.description: If true, search is case sensitive.

parameters.name: isRegex
parameters.description: If true, treats string parameter as regex.

commands.name: setAsyncCallStackDepth
commands.description: Enables or disables async call stacks tracking.

parameters.name: maxDepth
parameters.description:
Maximum depth of async call stacks. Setting to `0` will effectively disable collecting async
call stacks (default).

commands.name: setBlackboxPatterns
commands.description:
Replace previous blackbox patterns with passed ones. Forces backend to skip stepping/pausing in
scripts with url matching one of the patterns. VM will try to leave blackboxed script by
performing 'step in' several times, finally resorting to 'step out' if unsuccessful.

parameters.name: patterns
parameters.description: Array of regexps that will be used to check script url for blackbox state.

commands.name: setBlackboxedRanges
commands.description:
Makes backend skip steps in the script in blackboxed ranges. VM will try leave blacklisted
scripts by performing 'step in' several times, finally resorting to 'step out' if unsuccessful.
Positions array contains positions where blackbox state is changed. First interval isn't
blackboxed. Array should be sorted.

parameters.name: scriptId
parameters.description: Id of the script.

commands.name: setBreakpoint
commands.description: Sets JavaScript breakpoint at a given location.

parameters.name: location
parameters.description: Location to set breakpoint in.

parameters.name: condition
parameters.description:
Expression to use as a breakpoint condition. When specified, debugger will only stop on the
breakpoint if this expression evaluates to true.

returns.name: breakpointId
returns.description: Id of the created breakpoint for further reference.

commands.name: setBreakpointByUrl
commands.description:
Sets JavaScript breakpoint at given location specified either by URL or URL regex. Once this
command is issued, all existing parsed scripts will have breakpoints resolved and returned in
`locations` property. Further matching script parsing will result in subsequent
`breakpointResolved` events issued. This logical breakpoint will survive page reloads.

parameters.name: lineNumber
parameters.description: Line number to set breakpoint at.

parameters.name: url
parameters.description: URL of the resources to set breakpoint on.

parameters.name: urlRegex
parameters.description:
Regex pattern for the URLs of the resources to set breakpoints on. Either `url` or
`urlRegex` must be specified.

parameters.name: scriptHash
parameters.description: Script hash of the resources to set breakpoint on.

parameters.name: columnNumber
parameters.description: Offset in the line to set breakpoint at.

parameters.name: condition
parameters.description:
Expression to use as a breakpoint condition. When specified, debugger will only stop on the
breakpoint if this expression evaluates to true.

returns.name: breakpointId
returns.description: Id of the created breakpoint for further reference.

returns.name: locations
returns.description: List of the locations this breakpoint resolved into upon addition.

commands.name: setBreakpointsActive
commands.description: Activates / deactivates all breakpoints on the page.

parameters.name: active
parameters.description: New value for breakpoints active state.

commands.name: setPauseOnExceptions
commands.description:
Defines pause on exceptions state. Can be set to stop on all exceptions, uncaught exceptions or
no exceptions. Initial pause on exceptions state is `none`.

parameters.name: state
parameters.description: Pause on exceptions mode.

commands.name: setReturnValue
commands.description: Changes return value in top frame. Available only at return break position.

parameters.name: newValue
parameters.description: New return value.

commands.name: setScriptSource
commands.description: Edits JavaScript source live.

parameters.name: scriptId
parameters.description: Id of the script to edit.

parameters.name: scriptSource
parameters.description: New content of the script.

parameters.name: dryRun
parameters.description:
If true the change will not actually be applied. Dry run may be used to get result
description without actually modifying the code.

returns.name: callFrames
returns.description: New stack trace in case editing has happened while VM was stopped.

returns.name: stackChanged
returns.description: Whether current call stack  was modified after applying the changes.

commands.name: setSkipAllPauses
commands.description: Makes page not interrupt on any pauses (breakpoint, exception, dom exception etc).

parameters.name: skip
parameters.description: New value for skip pauses state.

commands.name: setVariableValue
commands.description:
Changes value of variable in a callframe. Object-based scopes are not supported and must be
mutated manually.

parameters.name: scopeNumber
parameters.description:
0-based number of scope as was listed in scope chain. Only 'local', 'closure' and 'catch'
scope types are allowed. Other scopes could be manipulated manually.

parameters.name: variableName
parameters.description: Variable name.

parameters.name: newValue
parameters.description: New variable value.

parameters.name: callFrameId
parameters.description: Id of callframe that holds variable.

commands.name: stepInto
commands.description: Steps into the function call.

parameters.name: breakOnAsyncCall
parameters.description:
Debugger will issue additional Debugger.paused notification if any async task is scheduled
before next pause.

commands.name: stepOut
commands.description: Steps out of the function call.

commands.name: stepOver
commands.description: Steps over the statement.

events.name: breakpointResolved
events.description: Fired when breakpoint is resolved to an actual script and location.

parameters.name: breakpointId
parameters.description: Breakpoint unique identifier.

parameters.name: location
parameters.description: Actual breakpoint location.

events.name: paused
events.description: Fired when the virtual machine stopped on breakpoint or exception or any other stop criteria.

parameters.name: callFrames
parameters.description: Call stack the virtual machine stopped on.

parameters.name: reason
parameters.description: Pause reason.

parameters.name: data
parameters.description: Object containing break-specific auxiliary properties.

parameters.name: hitBreakpoints
parameters.description: Hit breakpoints IDs

parameters.name: asyncStackTrace
parameters.description: Async stack trace, if any.

parameters.name: asyncStackTraceId
parameters.description: Async stack trace, if any.

parameters.name: asyncCallStackTraceId
parameters.description:
Just scheduled async call will have this stack trace as parent stack during async execution.
This field is available only after `Debugger.stepInto` call with `breakOnAsynCall` flag.

events.name: resumed
events.description: Fired when the virtual machine resumed execution.

events.name: scriptFailedToParse
events.description: Fired when virtual machine fails to parse the script.

parameters.name: scriptId
parameters.description: Identifier of the script parsed.

parameters.name: url
parameters.description: URL or name of the script parsed (if any).

parameters.name: startLine
parameters.description: Line offset of the script within the resource with given URL (for script tags).

parameters.name: startColumn
parameters.description: Column offset of the script within the resource with given URL.

parameters.name: endLine
parameters.description: Last line of the script.

parameters.name: endColumn
parameters.description: Length of the last line of the script.

parameters.name: executionContextId
parameters.description: Specifies script creation context.

parameters.name: hash
parameters.description: Content hash of the script.

parameters.name: executionContextAuxData
parameters.description: Embedder-specific auxiliary data.

parameters.name: sourceMapURL
parameters.description: URL of source map associated with script (if any).

parameters.name: hasSourceURL
parameters.description: True, if this script has sourceURL.

parameters.name: isModule
parameters.description: True, if this script is ES6 module.

parameters.name: length
parameters.description: This script length.

parameters.name: stackTrace
parameters.description: JavaScript top stack frame of where the script parsed event was triggered if available.

events.name: scriptParsed
events.description:
Fired when virtual machine parses script. This event is also fired for all known and uncollected
scripts upon enabling debugger.

parameters.name: scriptId
parameters.description: Identifier of the script parsed.

parameters.name: url
parameters.description: URL or name of the script parsed (if any).

parameters.name: startLine
parameters.description: Line offset of the script within the resource with given URL (for script tags).

parameters.name: startColumn
parameters.description: Column offset of the script within the resource with given URL.

parameters.name: endLine
parameters.description: Last line of the script.

parameters.name: endColumn
parameters.description: Length of the last line of the script.

parameters.name: executionContextId
parameters.description: Specifies script creation context.

parameters.name: hash
parameters.description: Content hash of the script.

parameters.name: executionContextAuxData
parameters.description: Embedder-specific auxiliary data.

parameters.name: isLiveEdit
parameters.description: True, if this script is generated as a result of the live edit operation.

parameters.name: sourceMapURL
parameters.description: URL of source map associated with script (if any).

parameters.name: hasSourceURL
parameters.description: True, if this script has sourceURL.

parameters.name: isModule
parameters.description: True, if this script is ES6 module.

parameters.name: length
parameters.description: This script length.

parameters.name: stackTrace
parameters.description: JavaScript top stack frame of where the script parsed event was triggered if available.

types.description: Sampling Heap Profile node. Holds callsite information, allocation statistics and child nodes.

properties.name: selfSize
properties.description: Allocations size in bytes for the node excluding children.

commands.name: addInspectedHeapObject
commands.description:
Enables console to refer to the node with given id via $x (see Command Line API for more details
$x functions).

parameters.name: heapObjectId
parameters.description: Heap snapshot object id to be accessible by means of $x command line API.

parameters.name: objectId
parameters.description: Identifier of the object to get heap object id for.

returns.name: heapSnapshotObjectId
returns.description: Id of the heap snapshot object corresponding to the passed remote object id.

parameters.name: objectGroup
parameters.description: Symbolic group name that can be used to release multiple objects.

returns.name: profile
returns.description: Return the sampling profile being collected.

parameters.name: samplingInterval
parameters.description:
Average sample interval in bytes. Poisson distribution is used for the intervals. The
default value is 32768 bytes.

parameters.name: reportProgress
parameters.description:
If true 'reportHeapSnapshotProgress' events will be generated while snapshot is being taken
when the tracking is stopped.

parameters.name: reportProgress
parameters.description: If true 'reportHeapSnapshotProgress' events will be generated while snapshot is being taken.

events.name: heapStatsUpdate
events.description: If heap objects tracking has been started then backend may send update for one or more fragments

parameters.name: statsUpdate
parameters.description:
An array of triplets. Each triplet describes a fragment. The first integer is the fragment
index, the second integer is a total count of objects for the fragment, the third integer is
a total size of the objects for the fragment.

events.name: lastSeenObjectId
events.description:
If heap objects tracking has been started then backend regularly sends a current value for last
seen object id and corresponding timestamp. If the were changes in the heap since last event
then one or more heapStatsUpdate events will be sent before a new lastSeenObjectId event.

types.description: Profile node. Holds callsite information, execution statistics and child nodes.

properties.name: hitCount
properties.description: Number of samples where this node was on top of the call stack.

properties.name: deoptReason
properties.description:
The reason of being not optimized. The function may be deoptimized or marked as don't
optimize.

properties.name: positionTicks
properties.description: An array of source position ticks.

properties.name: nodes
properties.description: The list of profile nodes. First item is the root node.

properties.name: timeDeltas
properties.description:
Time intervals between adjacent samples in microseconds. The first delta is relative to the
profile startTime.

types.description: Specifies a number of samples attributed to a certain source position.

properties.name: ticks
properties.description: Number of samples attributed to the source line.

types.description: Coverage data for a source range.

properties.name: startOffset
properties.description: JavaScript script source offset for the range start.

properties.name: endOffset
properties.description: JavaScript script source offset for the range end.

properties.name: count
properties.description: Collected execution count of the source range.

types.description: Coverage data for a JavaScript function.

properties.name: ranges
properties.description: Source ranges inside the function with coverage data.

properties.name: isBlockCoverage
properties.description: Whether coverage data for this function has block granularity.

types.description: Coverage data for a JavaScript script.

properties.name: functions
properties.description: Functions contained in the script that has coverage data.

types.description: Describes a type collected during runtime.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Name of a type collected with type profiling.

types.description: Source offset and types for a parameter or return value.

properties.name: offset
properties.description: Source offset of the parameter or end of function for return values.

properties.name: types
properties.description: The types for this parameter or return value.

types.description: Type profile data collected during runtime for a JavaScript script.

properties.name: entries
properties.description: Type profile entries for parameters and return values of the functions in the script.

commands.name: getBestEffortCoverage
commands.description:
Collect coverage data for the current isolate. The coverage data may be incomplete due to
garbage collection.

returns.name: result
returns.description: Coverage data for the current isolate.

commands.name: setSamplingInterval
commands.description: Changes CPU profiler sampling interval. Must be called before CPU profiles recording started.

parameters.name: interval
parameters.description: New sampling interval in microseconds.

commands.name: startPreciseCoverage
commands.description:
Enable precise code coverage. Coverage data for JavaScript executed before enabling precise code
coverage may be incomplete. Enabling prevents running optimized code and resets execution
counters.

parameters.name: callCount
parameters.description: Collect accurate call counts beyond simple 'covered' or 'not covered'.

parameters.name: detailed
parameters.description: Collect block-based coverage.

commands.name: startTypeProfile
commands.description: Enable type profile.

commands.name: stopPreciseCoverage
commands.description:
Disable precise code coverage. Disabling releases unnecessary execution count records and allows
executing optimized code.

commands.name: stopTypeProfile
commands.description: Disable type profile. Disabling releases type profile data collected so far.

commands.name: takePreciseCoverage
commands.description:
Collect coverage data for the current isolate, and resets execution counters. Precise code
coverage needs to have started.

returns.name: result
returns.description: Coverage data for the current isolate.

commands.name: takeTypeProfile
commands.description: Collect type profile.

returns.name: result
returns.description: Type profile for all scripts since startTypeProfile() was turned on.

parameters.name: location
parameters.description: Location of console.profileEnd().

parameters.name: title
parameters.description: Profile title passed as an argument to console.profile().

events.name: consoleProfileStarted
events.description: Sent when new profile recording is started using console.profile() call.

parameters.name: location
parameters.description: Location of console.profile().

parameters.name: title
parameters.description: Profile title passed as an argument to console.profile().

domains.description:
Runtime domain exposes JavaScript runtime by means of remote evaluation and mirror objects.
Evaluation results are returned as mirror object that expose object type, string representation
and unique identifier that can be used for further object reference. Original objects are
maintained in memory unless they are either explicitly released or are released along with the
other objects in their object group.

types.description: Primitive value which cannot be JSON-stringified.
Mirror object referencing original JavaScript object.

properties.name: subtype
properties.description: Object subtype hint. Specified for `object` type values only.

properties.name: className
properties.description: Object class (constructor) name. Specified for `object` type values only.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Remote object value in case of primitive values or JSON values (if it was requested).

properties.name: unserializableValue
properties.description:
Primitive value which can not be JSON-stringified does not have `value`, but gets this
property.

properties.name: preview
properties.description: Preview containing abbreviated property values. Specified for `object` type values only.

types.description: Object containing abbreviated remote object value.

properties.name: subtype
properties.description: Object subtype hint. Specified for `object` type values only.

properties.name: overflow
properties.description: True iff some of the properties or entries of the original object did not fit.

properties.name: entries
properties.description: List of the entries. Specified for `map` and `set` subtype values only.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Object type. Accessor means that the property itself is an accessor property.

properties.name: subtype
properties.description: Object subtype hint. Specified for `object` type values only.

properties.name: key
properties.description: Preview of the key. Specified for map-like collection entries.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The value associated with the property.

properties.name: writable
properties.description: True if the value associated with the property may be changed (data descriptors only).

properties.name: get
properties.description:
A function which serves as a getter for the property, or `undefined` if there is no getter
(accessor descriptors only).

properties.name: set
properties.description:
A function which serves as a setter for the property, or `undefined` if there is no setter
(accessor descriptors only).

properties.name: configurable
properties.description:
True if the type of this property descriptor may be changed and if the property may be
deleted from the corresponding object.

properties.name: enumerable
properties.description:
True if this property shows up during enumeration of the properties on the corresponding
object.

properties.name: wasThrown
properties.description: True if the result was thrown during the evaluation.

properties.name: isOwn
properties.description: True if the property is owned for the object.

properties.name: symbol
properties.description: Property symbol object, if the property is of the `symbol` type.

types.description: Object internal property descriptor. This property isn't normally visible in JavaScript code.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The value associated with the property.

types.description:
Represents function call argument. Either remote object id `objectId`, primitive `value`,
unserializable primitive value or neither of (for undefined) them should be specified.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Primitive value or serializable javascript object.

properties.name: unserializableValue
properties.description: Primitive value which can not be JSON-stringified.

properties.name: id
properties.description:
Unique id of the execution context. It can be used to specify in which execution context
script evaluation should be performed.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Human readable name describing given context.

types.description:
Detailed information about exception (or error) that was thrown during script compilation or
execution.

properties.name: text
properties.description: Exception text, which should be used together with exception object when available.

properties.name: lineNumber
properties.description: Line number of the exception location (0-based).

properties.name: columnNumber
properties.description: Column number of the exception location (0-based).

properties.name: scriptId
properties.description: Script ID of the exception location.

properties.name: url
properties.description: URL of the exception location, to be used when the script was not reported.

properties.name: executionContextId
properties.description: Identifier of the context where exception happened.

types.description: Stack entry for runtime errors and assertions.
Call frames for assertions or error messages.

properties.name: description
properties.description:
String label of this stack trace. For async traces this may be a name of the function that
initiated the async call.

properties.name: parent
properties.description: Asynchronous JavaScript stack trace that preceded this stack, if available.

properties.name: parentId
properties.description: Asynchronous JavaScript stack trace that preceded this stack, if available.

types.description:
If `debuggerId` is set stack trace comes from another debugger and can be resolved there. This
allows to track cross-debugger calls. See `Runtime.StackTrace` and `Debugger.paused` for usages.

commands.name: awaitPromise
commands.description: Add handler to promise with given promise object id.

parameters.name: promiseObjectId
parameters.description: Identifier of the promise.

parameters.name: returnByValue
parameters.description: Whether the result is expected to be a JSON object that should be sent by value.

parameters.name: generatePreview
parameters.description: Whether preview should be generated for the result.

returns.name: result
returns.description: Promise result. Will contain rejected value if promise was rejected.

returns.name: exceptionDetails
returns.description: Exception details if stack strace is available.

commands.name: callFunctionOn
commands.description:
Calls function with given declaration on the given object. Object group of the result is
inherited from the target object.

parameters.name: functionDeclaration
parameters.description: Declaration of the function to call.

parameters.name: objectId
parameters.description:
Identifier of the object to call function on. Either objectId or executionContextId should
be specified.

parameters.name: arguments
parameters.description:
Call arguments. All call arguments must belong to the same JavaScript world as the target
object.

parameters.name: silent
parameters.description:
In silent mode exceptions thrown during evaluation are not reported and do not pause
execution. Overrides `setPauseOnException` state.

parameters.name: returnByValue
parameters.description: Whether the result is expected to be a JSON object which should be sent by value.

parameters.name: generatePreview
parameters.description: Whether preview should be generated for the result.

parameters.name: userGesture
parameters.description: Whether execution should be treated as initiated by user in the UI.

parameters.name: awaitPromise
parameters.description:
Whether execution should `await` for resulting value and return once awaited promise is
resolved.

parameters.name: executionContextId
parameters.description:
Specifies execution context which global object will be used to call function on. Either
executionContextId or objectId should be specified.

parameters.name: objectGroup
parameters.description:
Symbolic group name that can be used to release multiple objects. If objectGroup is not
specified and objectId is, objectGroup will be inherited from object.

commands.name: compileScript
commands.description: Compiles expression.

parameters.name: expression
parameters.description: Expression to compile.

parameters.name: sourceURL
parameters.description: Source url to be set for the script.

parameters.name: persistScript
parameters.description: Specifies whether the compiled script should be persisted.

parameters.name: executionContextId
parameters.description:
Specifies in which execution context to perform script run. If the parameter is omitted the
evaluation will be performed in the context of the inspected page.

commands.name: disable
commands.description: Disables reporting of execution contexts creation.

commands.name: discardConsoleEntries
commands.description: Discards collected exceptions and console API calls.

commands.name: enable
commands.description:
Enables reporting of execution contexts creation by means of `executionContextCreated` event.
When the reporting gets enabled the event will be sent immediately for each existing execution
context.

commands.name: evaluate
commands.description: Evaluates expression on global object.

parameters.name: expression
parameters.description: Expression to evaluate.

parameters.name: objectGroup
parameters.description: Symbolic group name that can be used to release multiple objects.

parameters.name: includeCommandLineAPI
parameters.description: Determines whether Command Line API should be available during the evaluation.

parameters.name: silent
parameters.description:
In silent mode exceptions thrown during evaluation are not reported and do not pause
execution. Overrides `setPauseOnException` state.

parameters.name: contextId
parameters.description:
Specifies in which execution context to perform evaluation. If the parameter is omitted the
evaluation will be performed in the context of the inspected page.

parameters.name: returnByValue
parameters.description: Whether the result is expected to be a JSON object that should be sent by value.

parameters.name: generatePreview
parameters.description: Whether preview should be generated for the result.

parameters.name: userGesture
parameters.description: Whether execution should be treated as initiated by user in the UI.

parameters.name: awaitPromise
parameters.description:
Whether execution should `await` for resulting value and return once awaited promise is
resolved.

commands.name: getProperties
commands.description:
Returns properties of a given object. Object group of the result is inherited from the target
object.

parameters.name: objectId
parameters.description: Identifier of the object to return properties for.

parameters.name: ownProperties
parameters.description:
If true, returns properties belonging only to the element itself, not to its prototype
chain.

parameters.name: accessorPropertiesOnly
parameters.description:
If true, returns accessor properties (with getter/setter) only; internal properties are not
returned either.

parameters.name: generatePreview
parameters.description: Whether preview should be generated for the results.

returns.name: internalProperties
returns.description: Internal object properties (only of the element itself).

commands.name: globalLexicalScopeNames
commands.description: Returns all let, const and class variables from global scope.

parameters.name: executionContextId
parameters.description: Specifies in which execution context to lookup global scope variables.

domains.description: This domain exposes DOM read/write operations. Each DOM Node is represented with its mirror object that has an id. This id can be used to get additional information on the Node, resolve it into the JavaScript object wrapper, etc. It is important that client receives DOM events only for the nodes that are known to the client. Backend keeps track of the nodes that were sent to the client and never sends the same node twice. It is client's responsibility to collect information about the nodes that were sent to the client.

domains.description: This domain exposes CSS read/write operations. All CSS objects (stylesheets, rules, and styles) have an associated 'id' used in subsequent operations on the related object. Each object type has a specific 'id' structure, and those are not interchangeable between objects of different kinds. CSS objects can be loaded using the get*ForNode() calls (which accept a DOM node id). A client can also discover all the existing stylesheets with the getAllStyleSheets() method (or keeping track of the styleSheetAdded/styleSheetRemoved events) and subsequently load the required stylesheet contents using the getStyleSheet[Text]() methods.

types.description: Stylesheet type: "injected" for stylesheets injected via extension, "user-agent" for user-agent stylesheets, "inspector" for stylesheets created by the inspector (i.e. those holding the "via inspector" rules), "regular" for regular stylesheets.
